# there has been a discussion about how certain functions - ie. Ogre.Vector3.length() - have, due to bugs :) been hidden
# by autogenerated properties with the same name.  For example in early versions of Python-Ogre we generated a 'length'
# property for Vector3 that meant you had to do vect.lenght, NOT vect.length() 
#
# in the current Python-Ogre implementation this 'bug' has been fixed - however in investigating this problem we created
# a base list of the 'properties' that had previously been hidden - and have tested (briefly) the use of python "property"
# to create the previous behaviour.  This also allows people to make Python-Ogre work more like Pyogre..
#
# this code has not been tested, however you could insert (call) this early in your code to assist in conversion to Python-Ogre
#


Ogre.MovableObjectFactory.requestTypeFlags = property( Ogre.MovableObjectFactory.requestTypeFlags )
